  "texts": [
    "According to their experimental findings, the CRF [90], Bi-LSTM and CNN algorithms operate better together than the other basic techniques like Bi-LSTM, recurrent neural network (RNN) and long short-term (LSTM) alone.",
    "Fu et al. [91] presented a technique for labelling datasets of related languages and iterative optimization to create a Malay NER dataset (MS-NER) which comprises 20,146 sentences.",
    "Furthermore, the authors suggested MTBR, a Multi-Task framework to incorporate boundary information to perform better for NER.",
    "In addition, boundary detection is viewed as a support function, and a strengthened Bidirectional Revision module that includes a gated ignoring technique is suggested to handle conditional label transfer.",
    "They also conducted the depth experiments on Indonesian, English and Malay and the results of the experiments demonstrate that MTBR may perform competitively and frequently outperforms various baselines in which the created model and dataset would be made accessible to the general public as a fresh, trustworthy baseline for Malay NER."
  ],
